cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.NE 

This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.CL (Computation and Language) as it focuses on enhancing the sequential order awareness of CNN for sequence-to-sequence learning, which is a key topic in natural language processing. It could also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning) as it proposes a new model for deep learning. Additionally, since CNN is widely used in image processing, it could also belong to cs.CV (Computer Vision). The paper also involves the use of neural networks, which falls under the scope of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
